{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YbxhkQfqwXcbVcEvVBEb5K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap is created and the cluster is untouched. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Cluster state found (all non-default):**\n| Category | Item | Detail |\n|---|---|---|\n| Vhosts | `/app`, `/ops` | Both custom; only `/` is default |\n| Users | `admin` [administrator], `app-user` [management], `ops-user` [management] | All non-default (`guest` absent) |\n| Policies | `/app` → `ha-all` | `ha-mode=all`, `ha-sync-mode=automatic` |\n| Queues | `/app/app-queue`, `/ops/ops-queue` | Both classic, durable |\n| Permissions | `admin` on `/`, `/app`, `/ops`; `app-user` on `/app`; `ops-user` on `/ops` | All non-default |\n\n**What the rollback script does (5 ordered steps):**\n1. `clear_policy -p /app ha-all` — removes the HA mirror policy\n2. `delete_queue` for both `app-queue` and `ops-queue` (explicit, for audit trail)\n3. `delete_vhost /app` and `/ops` — cascades remaining exchanges/bindings/permissions\n4. `delete_user admin/app-user/ops-user` — also removes their `/` permissions\n5. Restores `guest:guest` with administrator tag + full perms on `/` if absent\n\nThe cluster configuration (vhosts, users, policies, queues) is identical to how it was found — only the ConfigMap was added."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":478,"cache_read_input_tokens":38549,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":478},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7b0dae4-dd1f-41a4-b0d2-cbbf9b9d9efd","uuid":"c0db5a08-1d68-4c9c-b7b2-e595d9e5e2bf","request_id":"req_011CcMUL7TttbZAgeCKigfig"}
